AUDIO: 'You\'ve probably talked to a voice AI recently and maybe it was frustrating. Maybe it cut you off. Maybe it felt robotic. Here\'s the thing. Building a voice agent that actually feels natural is harder than it looks. But once you understand the fundamentals, you can'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'build something that people genuinely want to talk to, don\'t mind talking to, and actually prefer to talk to. And that\'s what this workshop is about. You don\'t need prior experience with voice AI, machine learning, or real-time'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'systems. I\'ll explain all of those concepts as we go. Voice AI hit an inflection point. Speechtoext models are faster and more accurate. LLMs can handle nuanced conversations. Text to'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'speech sounds human. These pieces exist. The challenge is wiring them together into something that feels responsive and natural. Now, a year ago, building this required specialized engineering knowledge and months of hard work.'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Today, you can get a working voice agent running in just a few minutes. So, here\'s what you\'re going to learn throughout this workshop. First, how the voice pipeline works. That\'s VAD, ST, LLM, and TTS. And then, why latency'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'matters and how to uh minimize it. You\'ll learn techniques for natural turntaking so your agent doesn\'t interrupt you mid-sentence. You\'ll add personality to your agent and set up'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
